================
description
================

1) This program accept directory name from user and copy first 10 bytes from all regular
files into newly created file named as "output".
2) Required directory name will be taken from command line

================
about the code
================

	input	:	directory name
	output	:	result - 10 byets from each file will copy into "output" (regular) file.
 			
=============
How to run
=============

	make	:	compile the code and generates executable file as "myexe"
	make run:	run the executable with command line argument
			for this you have to pass parameter as: 
			
			$ make run p="parameter_value" 
	
=============
NOTE
=============

	1)If the given directory_file is unable to open, it will display the appropriate reason.
